'''Bogumiła Berdychowska''' (born 1964) is a [[Poles|Polish]] writer and journalist, often writing about the [[Polish minority in Russia|Polish minorities]] in the former [[USSR]] and their history.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.euranet.eu/pol/content/view/full/44892 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-03-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110720162933/http://www.euranet.eu/pol/content/view/full/44892 |archivedate=2011-07-20 |df= }}</ref>
She was the director of the [[Bureau of National Minorities]] in the [[Ministry of Culture and National Heritage (Poland)#Ministers of Culture and Art .281989-1999.29|Polish Ministry of Art and Culture]] (1989-1994), and the vice-director of the [[Polish Radio]] (1994-2002).<ref>[http://www.informaworld.com/smpp/content~content=a782514419&db=all "Democratization and European standards of National minority protection: Polish issues"], ''Democratization'', Volume 4, Issue 3 Autumn 1997 , pages 45 - 68, George Sanford</ref><ref>http://www.cpsa-acsp.ca/papers-2008/Dembinska.pdf</ref> Since 2003, she has been the Director of the [[stipend]]s department in [[Narodowe Centrum Kultury]] (National Center of Culture).<ref>http://www.nck.pl/artykul/688/odznaczenie-bogumily-berdychowskiej-{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
