In [[art]] and [[art criticism]], '''form and content''' are considered distinct aspects of a [[work of art]]. The term ''form'' refers to the work's style, techniques and media used, and how the [[Design elements and principles|elements of design]] are implemented. ''Content'', on the other hand, refers to a work's subject matter, or what is being depicted.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://arthistory.about.com/cs/reference/f/what_is_art.htm|title=How to Define Art|publisher=}}</ref>

Incongruity between form and content [[Form-versus-content humor|can be humorous]].

